Trakanon is shunned by other dragons for his part in starting the war with the Iksar. But dragons are forbidden to kill each other, one of their most sacred laws, so they allow him to live in his exile. <br>
<br>
He is in the condition you see him due to the magics unleased during the war, vile necromantic and shamanistic powers prevent his wounds from healing.<br>
<br>
The same applies to Vox and Nagafen, they attempted something very very bad, and rather than being killed, they were sent into exile. <br>
<br>
What they wanted to do was mate. <br>
<br>
Dragons of different colors are not allowed to do this. It happened once before in history, and the result was Kerafyrm. <br>
<br>
What transpired after Kerafyrm being born was the first war between dragonkind, and the cost of that war was higher than any could imagine, hence the injunction against killing their own kind.<br>
<br>
Jaled Dar was not killed by Zlandicar, but Zlandicar found his charred remains a tasty snack when they were interred in the Necropolis. <br>
<br>
Jaled Dar hates Trakanon, blaming him for his death, rather than Ganak. Ganak was merely doing what he had to do to preserve his empire and people. Trakanon started the war that led to that. This hatred is what keeps his spirit attached to this world.<br>
<br>
Zlandicar is also protected by the injunction that prevents dragon from killing dragon, something he twists to his advantage, as his diet consists entirely of the flesh of his kind, usually dead, but not always......<br>
<br>
.........<br>
<br>
<br>
Kerafyrm is more commonly known as The Sleeper. <p>Nadia Nightengale<BR>
